---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    {
      params: { slug: 'how-to-clean-ac-filter-at-home' },
      props: {
        title: 'How to Clean Your AC Filter at Home',
        seoTitle: 'How to Clean Your AC Filter at Home | Vishwakarma Aircon Jaipur',
        description: 'Step-by-step guide to cleaning your AC filter at home. Save money on servicing and improve cooling performance with this simple DIY maintenance tip.',
        date: 'March 5, 2026',
        author: 'Vishwakarma Aircon Team',
        content: [
          {
            heading: 'Why Cleaning Your AC Filter Matters',
            text: 'A clogged AC filter is one of the most common reasons your air conditioner stops cooling efficiently. Dust, dirt, and debris accumulate on the filter over time, blocking airflow and forcing the compressor to work harder. This not only reduces cooling performance but also drives up your electricity bill by 15-20%. In dusty cities like Jaipur, where summer temperatures regularly cross 45 degrees Celsius, a clean filter can make the difference between a comfortable home and a sweltering one.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'What You Will Need',
            text: 'You do not need any special tools for this task. Keep a soft brush or old toothbrush handy, along with mild liquid soap or detergent, a bucket of lukewarm water, a soft dry cloth, and optionally a vacuum cleaner with a brush attachment. The entire process takes about 10-15 minutes and should be done once every two weeks during heavy usage months like April through September.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Step 1: Turn Off the AC and Unplug It',
            text: 'Safety comes first. Switch off your air conditioner from the remote and then turn off the power supply at the plug or MCB. Wait for a minute before you begin working on the unit. This ensures there is no residual electrical charge and the internal fan has stopped spinning completely.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Step 2: Open the Front Panel and Remove the Filter',
            text: 'For split ACs, gently lift the front panel of the indoor unit upward until it clicks into the open position. You will see one or two mesh filters sitting in a frame. Carefully slide them out. For window ACs, remove the front grille by unscrewing or unclipping it, then pull the filter out. Handle the filters gently as they can be fragile, especially in older units.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Step 3: Clean the Filter',
            text: 'If the filter has light dust, simply use a vacuum cleaner with a soft brush attachment to remove the debris. For heavier buildup, soak the filter in a bucket of lukewarm water mixed with a few drops of mild detergent for 10 minutes. Then gently scrub both sides with a soft brush. Rinse under running water until the water runs clear. Never use hot water or harsh chemicals as they can damage the filter mesh.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Step 4: Dry and Reinstall',
            text: 'Shake off excess water and let the filter air dry completely in a shaded area. Do not place it in direct sunlight as UV rays can make the plastic brittle over time. Once fully dry, slide the filter back into its slot, close the front panel, and power the unit back on. You should immediately notice better airflow and cooler air coming from your AC.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'When to Call a Professional',
            text: 'If cleaning the filter does not improve performance, or if you notice the filter is torn, warped, or has a persistent odour even after washing, it may be time for a replacement or a deeper AC service. At Vishwakarma Aircon, we offer comprehensive AC servicing that includes deep coil cleaning, gas pressure checks, and drainage line clearing — everything beyond what a simple filter clean can address.',
          },
        ],
      },
    },
    {
      params: { slug: 'signs-ac-needs-servicing-before-summer' },
      props: {
        title: 'Signs Your AC Needs Servicing Before Summer',
        seoTitle: 'Signs Your AC Needs Servicing Before Summer | Vishwakarma Aircon Jaipur',
        description: 'Don\'t wait for your AC to break down in peak heat. Learn the 7 warning signs that your air conditioner needs professional servicing before summer arrives.',
        date: 'February 20, 2026',
        author: 'Vishwakarma Aircon Team',
        content: [
          {
            heading: 'Why Pre-Summer Servicing Is Essential',
            text: 'Jaipur summers are brutal, with temperatures soaring above 45 degrees Celsius from April through June. The worst time for your AC to break down is when you need it the most. Pre-summer servicing ensures your unit is in peak condition, prevents costly emergency repairs, and can extend the life of your air conditioner by several years. Think of it as a health checkup for your AC before the marathon of summer.',
          },
          {
            heading: '1. Weak or Reduced Airflow',
            text: 'If you stand in front of your AC and the air barely reaches you, something is wrong. Weak airflow usually indicates a clogged filter, blocked condenser coils, or a failing blower motor. While you can clean the filter yourself, coil cleaning and motor issues need a trained technician. Ignoring this sign means your AC works harder, consumes more electricity, and cools your room poorly.',
          },
          {
            heading: '2. AC Is Running but Not Cooling',
            text: 'This is one of the most common complaints we receive. Your AC blows air but it is not cold enough. The culprit is often low refrigerant gas due to a slow leak, a dirty evaporator coil, or a malfunctioning compressor. Low gas levels can also damage the compressor over time if left unchecked, turning a small repair into an expensive replacement.',
          },
          {
            heading: '3. Unusual Noises',
            text: 'A well-maintained AC runs quietly. If you hear grinding, squealing, rattling, or buzzing sounds, it usually points to loose parts, a worn-out fan belt, debris caught in the unit, or bearing issues in the motor. These sounds tend to get worse over time and can lead to sudden breakdowns if not addressed promptly.',
          },
          {
            heading: '4. Water Leaking from the Indoor Unit',
            text: 'Water dripping from your split AC indoor unit is a clear sign of a blocked drainage pipe. Over months of use, algae, dust, and dirt build up inside the drain line, preventing condensation water from flowing out properly. A professional service includes flushing and clearing the drain line to prevent water damage to your walls and furniture.',
          },
          {
            heading: '5. Bad Smell When AC Is On',
            text: 'A musty or foul odour coming from your AC usually means mould or bacteria have built up inside the unit, particularly on the evaporator coils and in the drain pan. This is not just unpleasant — it can trigger allergies, asthma, and respiratory issues. A deep cleaning service eliminates these harmful microorganisms and restores fresh, clean air.',
          },
          {
            heading: '6. Electricity Bills Are Higher Than Usual',
            text: 'If your electricity bill has jumped significantly without a change in usage habits, your AC may be the culprit. A poorly maintained AC can consume 20-30% more power than a well-serviced one. Dirty coils, low gas, and worn-out components all force the system to run longer and work harder, driving up energy costs.',
          },
          {
            heading: '7. AC Has Not Been Serviced in Over a Year',
            text: 'Even if your AC seems to be working fine, skipping annual maintenance is a risk. Wear and tear accumulates invisibly. Refrigerant levels drop slowly, dust builds up inside, and electrical connections can loosen. A yearly professional service catches these issues early, before they turn into expensive problems during the peak of summer when every technician in the city is booked solid.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Book Your Pre-Summer Service Today',
            text: 'At Vishwakarma Aircon, we recommend getting your AC serviced in February or March, well before the summer rush. Our comprehensive service includes filter and coil cleaning, gas level check, drainage clearing, electrical inspection, and a full performance test. With 20+ years of experience in Jaipur, we know how to keep your AC running perfectly when you need it most.',
          },
        ],
      },
    },
    {
      params: { slug: 'inverter-ac-vs-non-inverter' },
      props: {
        title: 'Inverter AC vs Non-Inverter — Which Should You Buy?',
        seoTitle: 'Inverter AC vs Non-Inverter AC — Which Should You Buy? | Vishwakarma Aircon',
        description: 'A detailed comparison of inverter and non-inverter ACs covering cost, electricity savings, cooling performance, noise, and which is best for Jaipur homes.',
        date: 'February 8, 2026',
        author: 'Vishwakarma Aircon Team',
        content: [
          {
            heading: 'Understanding the Core Difference',
            text: 'The fundamental difference between inverter and non-inverter ACs lies in how the compressor operates. A non-inverter AC (also called a fixed-speed AC) has a compressor that runs at a constant speed — it switches fully on when cooling is needed and fully off when the set temperature is reached. An inverter AC, on the other hand, has a variable-speed compressor that adjusts its speed continuously based on the cooling demand. Think of it like a car: a non-inverter AC is either at full throttle or parked, while an inverter AC smoothly adjusts its speed.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Electricity Consumption and Savings',
            text: 'This is where inverter ACs clearly win. Because the compressor does not constantly start and stop, an inverter AC uses 30-50% less electricity compared to a non-inverter AC of the same capacity. In Jaipur, where ACs run for 6-8 months a year and often 10-14 hours a day during peak summer, this translates to significant savings. A 1.5-ton inverter AC might save you Rs 3,000-5,000 per year on electricity compared to its non-inverter counterpart.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Cooling Performance',
            text: 'Inverter ACs provide more consistent and comfortable cooling. Since the compressor adjusts its speed rather than cycling on and off, the room temperature stays stable without the hot-cold fluctuations common with non-inverter models. Inverter ACs also cool the room faster initially because they can run the compressor at higher speeds when there is a large gap between the current and desired temperature.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Noise Levels',
            text: 'Non-inverter ACs tend to be noisier because the compressor starts and stops frequently, producing a noticeable click and hum each time. Inverter ACs run more quietly since the compressor operates continuously at varying low speeds. If your AC is in a bedroom or a quiet workspace, the difference in noise is very noticeable and an inverter model will provide a much more peaceful environment.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Upfront Cost',
            text: 'Non-inverter ACs are cheaper to purchase, typically costing Rs 5,000-10,000 less than an equivalent inverter model. For a 1.5-ton split AC, a decent non-inverter model starts around Rs 28,000-32,000, while a comparable inverter model starts at Rs 35,000-42,000. However, the higher upfront cost of an inverter AC is usually recovered within 2-3 years through electricity savings, especially with heavy usage.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Maintenance and Repair Costs',
            text: 'Inverter ACs have more sophisticated electronics and components, which can mean slightly higher repair costs if something goes wrong outside of warranty. The inverter PCB (printed circuit board) is an expensive component to replace. Non-inverter ACs have simpler mechanics and are generally cheaper and easier to repair. That said, inverter compressors experience less wear and tear due to smoother operation, so they tend to have fewer breakdowns overall.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Which Is Right for You?',
            text: 'Choose an inverter AC if you use your air conditioner for more than 8 hours daily, want lower electricity bills, prefer quieter operation, and can afford the higher upfront cost. Choose a non-inverter AC if you use the AC sparingly (a few hours daily or only on the hottest days), are on a tight budget, or need an AC for a space like a guest room that is not used frequently. For most homes in Jaipur where ACs run heavily for half the year, an inverter AC is the smarter long-term investment.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Need Help Choosing? We Can Help',
            text: 'At Vishwakarma Aircon, we help customers choose the right AC for their space, usage pattern, and budget. We work with all major brands including Daikin, LG, Samsung, Voltas, Blue Star, and more. Whether you decide on an inverter or non-inverter model, we provide professional installation with proper copper piping, electrical setup, and post-installation testing to ensure peak performance from day one.',
          },
        ],
      },
    },
    {
      params: { slug: 'ac-installation-cost-jaipur' },
      props: {
        title: 'How Much Does AC Installation Cost in Jaipur?',
        seoTitle: 'AC Installation Cost in Jaipur (2026) — Complete Price Guide | Vishwakarma Aircon',
        description: 'Complete breakdown of AC installation costs in Jaipur for 2026. Covers split AC, window AC, piping, brackets, electrical work, and labour charges.',
        date: 'January 25, 2026',
        author: 'Vishwakarma Aircon Team',
        content: [
          {
            heading: 'What Determines AC Installation Cost?',
            text: 'The total cost of installing an AC depends on several factors: the type of AC (split or window), the distance between the indoor and outdoor units, the length of copper piping required, whether a new electrical point is needed, the floor you live on, and whether any masonry or wall drilling is involved. Understanding these factors helps you budget accurately and avoid surprises.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Split AC Installation Cost Breakdown',
            text: 'A standard split AC installation in Jaipur typically costs between Rs 1,500 and Rs 3,500 for labour and basic materials. This includes wall mounting of the indoor unit, installing the outdoor unit on a bracket or stand, connecting up to 3 feet of copper piping (usually included with the AC), basic electrical wiring to the nearest plug point, drain pipe setup, and a vacuum and gas check. If additional copper piping is needed beyond the standard 3 feet, it costs Rs 400-600 per foot depending on the diameter.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Window AC Installation Cost',
            text: 'Window AC installation is simpler and generally costs between Rs 800 and Rs 1,500. This covers cutting or adjusting the window frame or wall sleeve, placing and levelling the unit, sealing gaps around the AC to prevent hot air entry, and connecting to a power outlet. If a new wall cutout is required (no existing window or sleeve), masonry charges of Rs 500-1,500 may apply depending on wall thickness and material.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Additional Costs to Consider',
            text: 'Several extras can add to your installation bill. A wall-mounted MS bracket for the outdoor unit costs Rs 500-1,200. An iron stand for ground-level placement is Rs 400-800. If you need a separate MCB or dedicated electrical line from your meter, expect Rs 800-2,000 depending on the distance. A voltage stabilizer, recommended in areas with power fluctuations, ranges from Rs 1,500-3,500. Drain pipe extension beyond the standard length costs Rs 50-80 per foot.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Cost by AC Tonnage',
            text: 'Larger AC units generally cost slightly more to install because they use thicker copper piping and heavier outdoor units that require sturdier brackets. For a 1-ton split AC, expect total installation costs of Rs 1,500-2,500. A 1.5-ton unit runs Rs 2,000-3,000, while a 2-ton unit costs Rs 2,500-3,500. These are approximate ranges and actual costs depend on your specific installation requirements.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'High-Rise and Difficult Installations',
            text: 'If you live on a higher floor and the outdoor unit needs to be installed in a difficult-to-access location, additional charges may apply. Installations above the 4th floor without a dedicated AC ledge may require safety equipment and extra manpower, adding Rs 500-1,500 to the cost. Similarly, if the outdoor unit must be placed far from the indoor unit (requiring piping runs of 15 feet or more), the additional piping and labour costs can add up.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'How to Save on Installation Costs',
            text: 'Here are a few tips to keep your installation costs reasonable. First, plan the placement of your indoor and outdoor units to minimise the copper piping distance — every extra foot adds cost. Second, ensure you have a suitable electrical point near the AC location before the technician arrives. Third, get the AC installed during the off-season (October to February) when technicians are less busy and may offer better rates. Fourth, ask for a complete quote upfront that includes all materials so there are no surprise charges.',
          },
          {
            heading: 'Why Choose Vishwakarma Aircon for Installation',
            text: 'At Vishwakarma Aircon, we believe in transparent, upfront pricing with no hidden charges. Before starting any installation, our technician surveys your space and provides a complete cost breakdown. We use high-quality copper piping, proper flaring tools, and vacuum pumps to ensure a leak-free, efficient installation. With 20+ years of experience across thousands of installations in Jaipur — from single-room homes to entire commercial buildings — you can trust us to get the job done right the first time. Contact us for a free installation quote.',
          },
        ],
      },
    },
  ];
}

const { slug } = Astro.params;
const { title, seoTitle, description, date, author, content } = Astro.props;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={seoTitle}
  description={description}
>
  <!-- ===== ARTICLE HEADER ===== -->
  <section class="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-500 to-cyan-400 pt-28 pb-16 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10">
      <svg class="absolute top-10 right-20 w-24 h-24 text-white" viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="currentColor">
        <polygon points="50,5 61,35 95,35 67,57 78,91 50,70 22,91 33,57 5,35 39,35"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 1440 80" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <path d="M0 80L60 70C120 60 240 40 360 35C480 30 600 40 720 45C840 50 960 50 1080 45C1200 40 1320 30 1380 25L1440 20V80H0Z" fill="#F8FAFC"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
      <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-6 text-sm font-medium">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"></polyline></svg>
        Back to Blog
      </a>
      <h1 class="font-heading font-extrabold text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-white leading-tight mb-6">
        {title}
      </h1>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 text-white/80 text-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H8a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"></circle></svg>
          <span>{author}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"></line><line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"></line><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"></line></svg>
          <span>{date}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== ARTICLE BODY ===== -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        {content.map((section: { heading: string; text: string }) => (
          <div class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl md:text-2xl text-deep-navy mb-3">
              {section.heading}
            </h2>
            <p class="text-slate-gray leading-relaxed">
              {section.text}
            </p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </article>

      <!-- Author Box -->
      <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-sky-50 rounded-2xl border border-sky-100">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-400 to-cyan-400 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-7 h-7 text-white" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H8a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"></circle></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-heading font-bold text-deep-navy">{author}</p>
            <p class="text-slate-gray text-sm mt-1">
              With 20+ years of experience in AC repair, installation, and commercial cooling solutions in Jaipur, our team shares practical tips to help you keep your home and office comfortable year-round.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CTA SECTION ===== -->
  <section class="bg-deep-navy py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-3xl text-white mb-4">Need Professional AC Service?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg mb-8">
        Whether it is repair, installation, or maintenance — Vishwakarma Aircon has you covered across Jaipur.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="bg-arctic-teal text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-heading font-bold text-lg hover:bg-ice-blue transition-colors inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2"
        >
          Get Free Quote
        </a>
        <a
          href="tel:9928731910"
          class="bg-white text-deep-navy px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-heading font-bold text-lg hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2"
        >
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07 19.5 19.5 0 0 1-6-6 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 4.11 2h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 .7 2.81 2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L8.09 9.91a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 16.92z"></path></svg>
          Call 9928731910
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
